      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "~~Wait, I think I'm misunderstanding this,~~ `-connect` does still check for \"0\" explicitly:\r\n```c++\r\n        if (connect.size() != 1 || connect[0] != \"0\") {\r\n            connOptions.m_specified_outgoing = connect;\r\n        }\r\n```\r\nIs this only for backwards compatibility?\r\nI checked that at least both `-noconnect` and `-connect=0` still work.\r\n\r\nWhereas `-debuglogfile` uses `IsArgNegated`:\r\n```\r\ng_logger->m_print_to_file = !gArgs.IsArgNegated(\"-debuglogfile\");\r\n```\r\nTested: `-nodebuglogfile` works, but `-debuglogfile=0` doesn't. This is the only argument that uses `IsArgNegated`.\r\n\r\n(all in all, this change is still correct, I think)",
